Pollo en Pepitoria
  --America's Test Kitchen

40 oz chicken thighs (~8 pieces) bone-in, trimmed
1 tbsp evoo
1 onion, chopped fine
3 garlic cloves, minced
1 bay leaf
1/4 tsp cinnamon
2/3 c dry sherry
1 c chicken broth
14.5 oz can whole peeled tomatoes, drained and chopped fine
2 hard cooked large eggs, peeled and yolks and whites separated
1/2 c slivered blanched almonds, toasted
pinch saffron threads, crumbled
2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley
1 1/2 tsp lemon juice
salt and pepper

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 300F. Pat thighs dry with paper towels and season both sides with 1 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp pepper. Heat oil in 12" skillet over high heat until just shimmering. Add thighs and brown on both sides, 10-12 min. Transfer thighs to large plate and pour off all but 2 tsp fat from skillet. Return skillet to medium heat, add onion and 1/4 tsp salt, and cook, stirring frequently, until just softened, ~3 min. Add 2 tsp garlic, baay leaf, and cinnamon, and cook until fragrant, ~1 min. Add sherry and cook, scraping up any fond, until sherry starts to thicken, ~2 min. Stir in broth and tomatoes and bring to simmer. Return thighs to skillet, cover, transfer to oven, and cook until chicken registers 195F, 45-50 min. Transfer thighs to serving platter, remove and discard skin, and cover loosely with foil to keep warm. While thighs cook, finely chop egg whites. Discard bay leaf. Transfer 3/4 c chicken cooking liquid , egg yolks, almonds, saffron, and remaining garlic to blender. Process until smooth, ~2 min, scraping down sides as needed. Return mixture to skillet. Add 1 tbsp parsley and lemon juice; bring to simmer over medium heat. Simmer, whisking frequently, until thickened, 3-5 min. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Pour sauce over chicken, sprinkle with remaining 1 tbsp parsley and egg whites, and serve.



Notes: sherry rec - Lustau Palo Cortado Penninsula Sherry
